NEW BLOG // link in bio. Today is the International Day Against Homophobia and Transphobia. #IDAHOT In honour of the day, I wanted to start a conversation on the impact of sexual and gender discrimination on mental health. Today's post features quotes and tweets from an interesting group of people. Here is one quote from Jodi Gray, a transgender woman living in #Canada. .
.
“I am fortunate to live in a city that is more LGBT friendly than most. I still have experienced discrimination, though. The discrimination I have experienced in the healthcare system seems to be based on a lack of education rather than hate or hostility. I think the distinction is important when trying to address discrimination, but unfortunately, the effect on individuals trying to get help for a mental illness is no different. It seems to me, as a transgender woman, that instead of treating me as an individual, mental health professionals can only focus on my gender. Because my mental illness is not related to my gender, I do not feel I am getting the treatment I need.”
.
.

Today I fear a little less. 💕

Change is possible. Happiness is possible. Authenticity is possible. But all of these things take time and effort and perseverance and self love. Still, they are ever possible; so, never forget this, my friends. Never give up on yourselves.
Also, recognize that this picture is a total simplification of my journey. I did not wake up one day and just become a man, nor was I ever truly a woman. I have always been me -- whether dressed in a gown or a tie. Between and before these pictures are hundreds of days of incredibly important discovery and pain and growth that I will never ignore.
—
Left: June 2014, my senior prom. Right: May 2017, a friend's senior prom.

Vorsicht Trigger Warnung!! Ich fühle mich heute so unwohl wie schon lange nicht mehr. In meiner Jeans fühle ich mich fett, möchte wieder meine Jogginghose anziehen, denn dort zeichnet es meine Beine nicht ab. Ich bin so froh, dass ich jetzt Therapie habe denn ich halte meinen jetzigen Zustand nicht aus. Die Gedanken schreien mich an. Heute trage ich auch eine Jacke obwohl es so warm ist, aber ich kann mich nicht so zerschnitten zeigen. Möchte auch keinen anderen Patient in der Praxis triggern..
Naja aufjedenfall wünsche ich euch einen schönen warmen Tag.

P.s: ich war beim Tätowierer, er wollte mich heute schkn tätowieren aber meine Mutter wollte nach der Therapie nachhause und ich muss auch noch unsere Tiere füttern... #recovery #recoveryisworthit #anorexìanervosa #essstörung #edfighter #borderline #borderlinepersonalitydisorder #depressd #ssv #svv #warrior #fighter #staystrong

You have to hold on, teeth gritted, weary eyed. You have to keep fighting, keep hoping, keep dreaming, keep reaching for that thing 💪🏻✨ That BETTER thing they all say exists in the freedom from our own thoughts. You have to, above all, keep living as though life is the most beautiful thing you were ever given 🙏🏻🌸🌿 If you don't, your mind will only eat away at itself until there is nothing left.......your existence will be a mere shadow of misery 💀 The more you give in the more you lose of, not only yourself, but also your strength and will to continue. The more you give in, the more you lose what could and does belong to you. And before you know it, your life will have gone 🙈 Never stop believing, that maybe, the better thing IS out there waiting for you.....
